TODO: ship pre-built plugin JAR alongside the source tree

Today the only way to get motoko-client-plugin-1.0.0-SNAPSHOT.jar
is `mvn -DskipTests package` from a clone.  README's "Without Nix"
section assumes the user is happy to build.  For consumers who
already have openapi-generator-cli installed (Homebrew / sdkman /
manual JAR) but don't want a Java/Maven toolchain just to get a
38 KB plugin JAR, we should publish pre-builts.

## Three channels, ranked by friction

1. **GitHub Releases asset (recommended)** — `gh release create`
   + JAR upload per version. Trivially scriptable inside the
   plugin-scoped CI workflow (reminder on 754254c70c3) — tag-push
   triggers a build + publish step.  Consumer side:
     curl -L -o motoko-client-plugin.jar \
       https://github.com/ggreif/motoko-openapi-client-gen/releases/download/<tag>/motoko-client-plugin.jar
   then drop on classpath alongside openapi-generator-cli.jar.
   Zero infrastructure cost beyond the workflow.

2. **JitPack** — zero setup on our side; users add
   `com.github.ggreif.motoko-openapi-client-gen:motoko-client-plugin:<tag>`
   and JitPack builds on demand.  Adds a JitPack repo to consumers'
   pom.xml.  Free.

3. **Maven Central / Sonatype OSS** — the "proper" way.  Requires
   GPG signing, namespace verification, separate release pipeline.
   With our pom's <scope>provided</scope> on openapi-generator, the
   only consumers who benefit are Maven-native projects pulling the
   plugin via coordinates — which is a small audience.  Skip unless
   demand materialises.

## Design decisions to make before shipping

A. **Versioning scheme.** Two reasonable choices:
   - `v7.22.0-mot.1` (upstream-major.minor + our patch counter) —
     makes the compatibility surface legible at a glance.  When
     nixpkgs bumps openapi-generator-cli to 7.23.x we'd retag.
   - `v1.0.0` independent semver — conventional but hides the
     upstream coupling.  Compatibility lives in CHANGELOG + README.

B. **README restructure.** Once releases exist the "Without Nix"
   section should lead with `curl <release-url>`, demoting
   `mvn package` to "or build from source".  Order matters: the
   download-and-go path should be the front door.

C. **What about the parent repo's existing structure?** The
   plugin JAR target/ dir is currently in .gitignore (correctly).
   The release artefact lives at
   modules/motoko-client-plugin/target/motoko-client-plugin-1.0.0-SNAPSHOT.jar
   — the CI workflow uploads from there.  No tree changes needed.

## Coupling to plugin-scoped CI (reminder on 754254c70c3)

This is a natural follow-on to the CI work.  Single workflow:
  on: push to tags matching v*
  jobs:
    build-and-test (the gate steps from the CI reminder)
    publish-jar:
      needs: build-and-test
      runs: gh release create <tag> .../motoko-client-plugin.jar
Don't ship the CI without this; don't ship the artefact pipeline
without the gate.

## When to act

After the plugin-scoped CI is in place and stable for a couple of
client refreshes.  Trigger phrases: any user (internal or external)
asking "can I just download the plugin JAR without building it",
or any prep for making the repo more discoverable to non-Caffeine
Motoko developers.

