TODO: source motoko-client-plugin's openapi-generator dep from the
nix store, not Maven Central — single source of truth

Today modules/motoko-client-plugin/pom.xml has:

  <dependency>
    <groupId>org.openapitools</groupId>
    <artifactId>openapi-generator</artifactId>
    <version>7.22.0</version>
    <scope>provided</scope>
  </dependency>

Maven resolves this from Maven Central.  Meanwhile nixpkgs (via
flake.nix) already provides the byte-identical 7.22.0 build of
openapi-generator-cli at ${pkgs.openapi-generator-cli}/share/java/
openapi-generator-cli.jar.

The duplication means build-time and runtime versions can drift if
we forget to bump the pom in lockstep with a nixpkgs update.
Single source of truth would protect against that — a nixpkgs
bump would automatically become the build dep too.

## Subtlety: library JAR vs all-in-one CLI JAR

Maven Central serves two related artefacts:
  - org.openapitools:openapi-generator:7.22.0      (library JAR)
  - org.openapitools:openapi-generator-cli:7.22.0  (assembly JAR
    bundling library + all transitive deps via maven-shade-plugin)

Our pom depends on the LIBRARY.  Nixpkgs ships only the
all-in-one CLI assembly (the artefact a user actually invokes).
So we can't just point Maven at the nix store and call it done —
we'd need to either:

  (a) Extract/install the library jar from the CLI assembly,
  (b) Use the CLI assembly directly as the compile dep — depends
      whether maven-shade-plugin relocated the org.openapitools.
      codegen.* packages we extend (probably not; those are the
      API surface), or
  (c) Add a flake.nix shellHook that mvn install:install-file's
      the CLI assembly with the library's coordinates (works only
      if Maven doesn't need a real .pom for transitive deps —
      <scope>provided</scope> means we don't ship transitives,
      but mvn compile still needs them to resolve symbols).

(c) is the most plausible if we verify the symbol-resolution
story.  Or extract the pom from the CLI assembly's META-INF/maven/
and install both files.

## When to act

After the basic CI is stable (current sprint).  Trigger phrases:
"nixpkgs bumped openapi-generator-cli to X.Y", "build dep drift",
or any cycle where someone notices the plugin compiles but the
runtime CLI rejects a config (a version-skew symptom).

